The paper deals with a prevalent problem in machine learning, which is estimating the dependences between random variables and ranking them accordingly. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses information-theoretic approaches, which could place it in the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper proposes a new measure for ranking dependences, which could place it in the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses regularizing parameter estimates in a graphical model, which could place it in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
